         "received_events_url" : "https://api.github.com/users/laanwj/received_events",
         "repos_url" : "https://api.github.com/users/laanwj/repos",
         "site_admin" : false,
         "starred_url" : "https://api.github.com/users/laanwj/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
         "subscriptions_url" : "https://api.github.com/users/laanwj/subscriptions",
         "type" : "User",
         "url" : "https://api.github.com/users/laanwj"
      }
   },
   {
      "body" : "`fs::create_directory` is designed to return without error if the directory already exists.  So it works fine in the situations where a directory already exists, or a directory doesn't already exist.  However when there is a symlink in place of the directory which points to the NTFS partition it throws an error.  Resolving the path prior to the call to fs::create_directory avoids the issue as it reverts to one of the first two mentioned cases.",
